<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Array-Bounds on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/array-bounds/</link><description>Recent content in Array-Bounds on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/array-bounds/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] MATLAB Index Exceeds Array Bounds</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/matlab/matlab-index-out-of-range/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/matlab/matlab-index-out-of-range/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;MATLAB uses 1-based indexing. When you access an element beyond the array&amp;rsquo;s size, you get &amp;ldquo;Index exceeds the number of array elements&amp;rdquo; error.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;0-based indexing (from other languages)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Off-by-one error in loop bounds&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Array smaller than expected&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dynamic array shrunk after allocation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-matlab" data-lang="matlab"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% WRONG: 0-based indexing&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;a = [&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;disp(a(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;)) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% Error: index exceeds array bounds&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% CORRECT: 1-based indexing&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;disp(a(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;)) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% 1&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-matlab" data-lang="matlab"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% WRONG: Loop goes past array end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;arr = [&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;20&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;30&lt;/span&gt;];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; i = &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; disp(arr(i)) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% Error at i=4&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% CORRECT: Use array length&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; i = &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;:length(arr)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; disp(arr(i))
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-matlab" data-lang="matlab"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;a = [&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;a(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% Error: index exceeds array bounds&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;a(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;) = &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;4&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% Valid: extends array&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="matlab-dimension-mismatch"&gt;Dimension Mismatch&lt;/a&gt; - array compatibility&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="matlab-undefined-function"&gt;Undefined Function&lt;/a&gt; - function errors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] MATLAB Index Exceeds Array Bounds Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/matlab/index-out-of-bounds/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/matlab/index-out-of-bounds/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="matlab-index-exceeds-array-bounds-error-fix"&gt;MATLAB Index Exceeds Array Bounds Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This error occurs when you try to access an array element at an index that is greater than the size of the array. The message reads: &lt;code&gt;Index exceeds the number of array elements.&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;MATLAB arrays are 1-indexed, meaning the first element is at index 1. Any attempt to access index 0, a negative index, or an index larger than the array&amp;rsquo;s current size will trigger this error. It commonly appears when loops iterate beyond array boundaries or when dynamic resizing is not accounted for.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>